ies, who not only have begun suffering at a time when the Germans were having a very good time, but who, moreover, suffered for a just cause.

When I have to choose between giving for a Greek, Czech, French, Belgian, Chinese, Dutch, Norwegian, Russian, Jewish or German child, I shall not choose the latter one.

Very sincerely yours,





TO: KIRILL NABOKOV

1945

ALS, 2 pp.

8 Craigie Circle

Cambridge, Mass.

Dear Cyril,

I was very happy to get news from you and learn that you are safe. Almost